data.text:
The Omaha, NE & Council Bluffs, IA Wall Map, 2018 3rd Edition, measures 76" x 60" and is printed in complete street detail at a scale of 1 inch = 2,583 feet. This Omaha wall map provides up-to-date cartography with new streets and changes. Printed in color with a markable/washable-laminated surface. Streets are indexed in a separate book-format. Includes hanging rails top and bottom.

Omaha Wall Map coverage and boundaries include:

All of Douglas and Sarpy County

North: to the Douglas/Washington County Line

South: to the Platte River to include State Park and Louisville

East: to include all of Council Bluffs, IA

West: to the Memphis State Recreational Area including Ashland and Yutan.

Inset of downtown Omaha.

Omaha, NE & Council Bluffs, IA Wall Map Details include:

All streets and highways, government buildings, airports, golf courses and country clubs, railroads, zip codes and zip code boundaries, shopping centers, recreational parks, cemeteries, educational facilities, hospitals, post offices, city limits (color coded), fire and police stations, community names, and miscellaneous points of interest.
